// click_frame.su — click→substrate-state INTERACTION driving a whole-frame render.
//
// Combines toggle.su's substrate-state flip with frame_whole.su's one-op render: a
// click flips a 0/1 state ON THE SUBSTRATE, and the rendered frame is the glow GATED
// by that state — visible when the state is 1, blank when 0. The interaction's state
// lives in the substrate recur slot across clicks (never round-tripping through a host
// scalar between clicks); the host reads it only to drive the render (display boundary).
//
//   flip()                       — one click. Toggles the recurring 0/1 state on the
//                                  substrate (make_real(1.0) - state) and returns it.
//   frame_gated(x, y, ones, gate)— the glow gated by `gate` (the state, broadcast):
//                                  hadamard(gate, 1 - x^2 - y^2). gate=1 -> glow,
//                                  gate=0 -> all zeros (blank). One substrate op.
function vector flip() {
    recurring vector state = make_real(0.0);
    vector new_state = make_real(1.0) - state;
    recur(new_state);
    return new_state;
}

function vector frame_gated(vector x, vector y, vector ones, vector gate) {
    vector glow = ones - hadamard(x, x) - hadamard(y, y);
    return hadamard(gate, glow);
}

// Sanity entry: first click flips the state 0 -> 1.
function vector main() { return flip(); }
